hat there's nothing wrong in voting against nominees who don't appear to share a broader vision of what the constitution is about." (aaron blake, "(candidate last) vows to look into high court nominees' hearts," <em>the hill</em>, 7/17/07) </p><p><b>former sen. (candidate full) (d-nc) cites liberal justice ruth bader ginsberg as his ideal judge.</b> nbc's brian williams: "the question is, your model supreme court justice?" sen. (candidate last): "ginsberg or breyer." (msnbc (PARTY NAME) presidential debate, columbia, sc, 4/26/07) </p><p><b> <u>the (PARTY NAME) opposed strict constructionist judges:</u> </b> </p><p><b>sen. (candidate last) and sen. (candidate last) voted against the nomination of supreme court chief justice john roberts.</b> (roberts nomination, cq vote #245: confirmed 78-22: r 55-0; d 22-22; i 1-0, 9/29/05, (candidate last) and (candidate last) voted nay) </p><p><b>sen. (candidate last) and sen. (candidate last) voted against the nomination of supreme court justice samuel alito.</b> (alito nomination, cq vote #2: confirmed 58-42: r 54-1; d 4-40; i 0-1, 1/31/06, (candidate last) and (candidate last) voted nay) </p><p><b>sen. (candidate last) called judge alito "way out of the mainstream" and "dangerous."</b> ((candidate full) for president website, <a href="http://(candidate full).com/news/newsletter/alito20060112/index.html">http://(candidate full).com/news/newsletter/alito20060112/index.html</a>, accessed 6/12/07) </p><p><b> <u>the (PARTY NAME) opposed the supreme court's decision upholding the partial birth abortion ban:</u> </b> </p><p><b>sen. (candidate last) decried the supreme court's gonzalez v. carhart decision, calling it an "erosion of... constitutional rights."</b> (sen. (candidate full), "statement of senator hillary rodham (candidate last) on supreme court's gonzales v. carhart decision," press release, 4/18/07) </p><p><b>sen. (candidate last): "i strongly disagree with today's supreme court ruling, which dramatically departs from previ